# Technical Design & Multi-Review Process

Based on the requirement analysis document, deliver a complete technical design solution.

Then conduct review and evaluation sequentially from three perspectives: **Architect, Security Engineer, and QA Engineer**. Each role shall put forward specific problems and optimization suggestions for the solution.

Finally, integrate all review comments to deliver the revised and finalized technical design solution in standard Markdown format.

---

## Review Requirements for Each Role

### Architect Perspective
- Whether detailed logs are recorded during interface invocation to facilitate troubleshooting.
- Whether unnecessary technical complexity is introduced; whether there exist cross-layer invocation or circular dependency issues.
- Evaluate system scalability; identify potential performance bottlenecks if user traffic increases by 10 times.
- Provide targeted modification and optimization suggestions.

### Security Engineer Perspective
- Check for risks of unauthorized access and data leakage at the interface and data levels.
- Verify whether permission verification and interface authentication are implemented for relevant interfaces.
- Provide targeted modification and optimization suggestions.

### QA Engineer Perspective
- Identify scenarios in the solution that are difficult to test and determine whether special test data needs to be constructed.
- Check whether boundary scenarios, exception processes and fault tolerance logic are fully considered in the design.
- Sort out testing difficulties and potential missed-test risks.
- Provide targeted modification and optimization suggestions.
